To engineer the titania particles’ properties, we begin by slowing-down the reaction kinetics in an attempt to synthesize amorphous TiO2 material rich in oxygen vacancies. Most common alkoxy groups used in the TiO2 synthesis contain between two carbon atoms (ethoxy) and four carbon atoms (butoxy). Their reactivity towards hydrolysis decreases as the number of carbon atoms in the chain increases58. To decrease their reactivity towards water, it is common to dilute the nanoparticles in alcohols or mix with complexing agents58. In our case, acetylacetone (acac) is used as a complexing agent in order to chelate the metallic cation on the Ti(OBu)4. The reaction between acac and Ti(OBu)4 occurs trough an interexchange substitution mechanism and it can be represented as follows58:TiOBun4+acacH→TiOBun4-x+xBuOH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
